<p>Secondly, after the slot has rolled for the cost of the champion, it rolls from the pool of champions with that cost. There are 29 copies of each unique 1-cost champion, 22 copies of 2-cost champions, 18 copies of 3-cost champions, 12 copies of 4-cost champions, and 10 copies of 5-cost champions<span class="sidenote-number"></span><span class="sidenote"><a href="https://teamfighttactics.leagueoflegends.com/en-gb/news/game-updates/teamfight-tactics-patch-9-22-notes/">Patch 9.22 notes</a> and <a href="https://teamfighttactics.leagueoflegends.com/en-gb/news/game-updates/teamfight-tactics-patch-10-12-notes/">patch 10.12 notes</a>.</span>. Furthermore, we have to know the amount of unique champions for each cost. You can count these up yourself, but there are 13 unique 1-, 2-, and 3-cost champions, 11 unique 4-cost champions, and 8 unique 5-cost champions.</p>

